title: Maryland softball team stuns No. 1 Florida, 4-2
text:
The Maryland women's softball team collected its first bid since 1999. And the team was shipped out to ... College Park.
Yes, the Terps not only got into the NCAA tournament but they are playing host to one of 16 sites.

And speaking of NCAA tournaments...

Yes, the Terps not only got into the NCAA tournament but they are playing host to one of 16 sites. 
The Terps (33-22, 8-11 ACC) open against... (Jeff Barker) 
Cleanup hitter Madison Martin went 3-for-4 for the Terps and earned the save in relief of winning pitcher Hannah Dewey, who gave up one earned run in 5 1/3 innings. 
Maryland's first three batters in the lineup — Skylynne Ellazar, Anna Kufta and Kristina Dillard — each had two hits.
